data.content:
## What breaks: Sync I/O on Cosmos DB is **fully removed** in EF Core 11

In .NET 10, you could opt into sync-over-async for the Cosmos provider. In EF Core 11, **that opt-in no longer exists** — all synchronous calls (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) **always throw** at runtime. There is no workaround.

### Fix: Convert everything to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple through callers — every call site must `await` the new async methods, propagating `async`/`Task` up the chain.

**Also watch for** (with Cosmos + EF Core 11): empty owned collections now return `[]` instead of `null`, so update any `is null` checks to `.Count == 0`.
